set cannot be\nused as part of the real infrastructure to\nproduce sales.\n\nImproper capitalization of an expense as an asset.\nFor example, WorldCom's line-cost expense was\nmisclassified as PPE.\n\nThis could signal understatement of expenses via\nomitting to record the expenses, or by deferring\nthe expenses, or by improper capitalization of the\nexpenses\n\nUnderstatement of expenses via “lack of accrual.”\n\nUnderstatement of expenses via deferral of\nexpenses.\n\nFailure to record asset impairments.\n\nUnderstatement of bad debts expense.\n\nAcceleration of revenue via improper use\nof multiple-element contracts through\nmisclassification of revenue streams.\n\nAggressive recognition of revenue that will be\nearned only in future periods.\n\nAllowance for returns may be understated.\n\n(continued)\n''"
